<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1132/14: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jeffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-26T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 26,
                                        1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 7
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>75. Department’s 44, October 23, 6 p.m. Am officially informed that
                            President Brum and the officials of the Government will be greatly
                            pleased and feel highly honored by visit from Secretary Colby. As the
                            Uruguayan elections occur on November 28th it is suggested the Secretary
                            should not arrive at Montevideo on this date nor Friday or Saturday
                            preceding.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jeffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>